//object.js
class Pet {
    constructor(name, image, species) {
        this.name = name
        this.image = image
        this.species = species
    }

}

class Trainer {
    constructor(name, image, experience, pets = []) {
        this.name = name
        this.image = image
        this.experience = experience
        this.pets = pets
    }

    static describeClass() {
        console.log('This is a trainer class whos constructor takes a name, experience, and image attribute',this)

    }

    sayName() {
        console.log(`my name is ${this.name}`)
    }

    listPets() {
        if (this.pets.length > 0) {
            this.pets.forEach(pet => console.log(pet.name))
        } else {
            console.log('I do not have any trained pets yet.')
        }
    }

   render() {
        let trainerCard = `
                <div class="card">
                <img src="${this.image}"></img>
                <h1>Name: ${this.name}</h1>
                <h3>Experience: ${this.experience}</h3>
                <ul class="pet-list" >Pets:</ul>
                ${ this.pets.map(pet => `<li>${pet.name}</li>` )}
              </div>`

       let ul = document.querySelector('.pet-list')

        return trainerCard
   }

    addPet(pet) {
        this.pets.push(pet)
    }
}

let pikachu = new Pet('pikachu', "data:image/jpeg;base64,", 'pokemon')
let ash = new Trainer('ash', "data:image/jpeg;base64,", 5)




//index.js
document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", setupCode)

// let setupCode = () => console.log('inside setup code')
let cardColumn = document.querySelector('.card-columns')

function setupCode() {
    console.log('inside setup code')
    // let formButton = ($('.form').get(0))
    let formButton = document.querySelector('.form')
    formButton.addEventListener('submit', handleSubmit)

    console.log(ash)
    ash.addPet(pikachu)


    let cardContainer = document.querySelector('.card-columns')
    cardContainer.innerHTML += ash.render()

}

function handleSubmit(event) {
    event.preventDefault()
    console.log('inside handle submit:')
    const [image, name, experience] = event.target
    console.log(image, name, experience)
    let newTrainerTemplate = new Trainer(name.value, image.value, experience.value)
    console.log(newTrainerTemplate)
    let cardContainer = document.querySelector('.card-columns')
    cardContainer.innerHTML += newTrainerTemplate.render()

}
